# STRATEGICLAND — Color System

> Color is **temperature**, not decoration.
> The palette is **warm, low-saturation, and editorial** — closer to a developed photograph than a digital UI.
> If a color "pops", it's wrong.

---

## 1. Color Philosophy

- The project rejects **pure black** and **pure white**. Both read as digital, both flatten atmosphere.
- All neutrals carry a slight **warmth** (toward amber/cream) or **coolness** (toward graphite). Never pure gray.
- Accents are **rare**, **muted**, and **chapter-specific**. There is no "brand orange".
- Saturated colors are forbidden by default. Saturation maxes at **40%** for any visible color.
- Gradients are **atmospheric** (radial, soft) — never **directional** (linear, decorative).

---

## 2. Core Palette (LOCKED)

### 2.1 Warm Black System
The project's foundational dark colors. All "black" in the project resolves to one of these.

| Token            | Hex        | HSL            | Use                                  |
|------------------|------------|----------------|--------------------------------------|
| `bg.warmBlack`   | `#0A0907`  | hsl(30 14% 3%) | Default dark page background         |
| `bg.coolBlack`   | `#0B0D10`  | hsl(214 13% 5%)| Cool variant; Human chapter only     |
| `bg.charcoal`    | `#161310`  | hsl(24 10% 7%) | Elevated surface (used rarely)       |

