## 3. Restrained Accent System

The project allows **at most 6 accent colors**, each tied to a specific chapter palette. **Never** invent additional accents.

| Token            | Hex        | HSL              | Bound Chapter / Use                 |
|------------------|------------|------------------|-------------------------------------|
| `accent.amber`   | `#C8923C`  | hsl(36 56% 51%)  | Cultural chapters (warm climaxes)    |
| `accent.copper`  | `#9E5A38`  | hsl(18 49% 42%)  | Cultural / heritage tones            |
| `accent.moss`    | `#5A6B45`  | hsl(85 20% 35%)  | Drift / human chapters (earthy)      |
| `accent.slate`   | `#3D4A55`  | hsl(208 17% 29%) | Editorial / case study cool          |
| `accent.parchment`| `#D9C49A` | hsl(40 49% 73%)  | Used as muted highlight on dark      |
| `accent.ember`   | `#A33A1F`  | hsl(11 68% 38%)  | Climactic moments only (≤ 1× per page)|

### Constraints
- Each chapter declares **at most 1 accent** in its `atmosphere.config.ts`.
- Accents are used for: link hovers, chapter eyebrows, text-as-emphasis, subtle ambient overlays.
- Accents are **never** used for buttons, badges, tags, "highlight cards".
- Maximum **2 accents visible per page** (across all chapters).

---

## 4. Atmospheric Tint Layers

Used as `mix-blend-mode: multiply` overlays at low opacity to grade scenes.

| Token              | Hex        | Use                                            |
|--------------------|------------|------------------------------------------------|
| `tint.warmFog`     | `#3A2D1E`  | Warm fog grade (drift / cultural)              |
| `tint.coolFog`     | `#1F2B30`  | Cool fog grade (human / editorial)             |
| `tint.amberDust`   | `#5A3F1A`  | Amber dust grade (climactic / cultural)        |
| `tint.coolPaper`   | `#1F252A`  | Cool grade for light backgrounds (rare)        |

### Constraints
- Tint overlays applied at **3–8% opacity max**.
- Always `mix-blend-mode: multiply` on dark scenes; `mix-blend-mode: overlay` on light scenes.
- Animated transitions between chapter tints during seam transitions (see `transition-system.mdc`).

---

## 5. Cinematic Gradients (radial only)

The project uses **only radial gradients**, used as atmospheric ambient lighting.

### Allowed gradient patterns
| Pattern              | Implementation                                                                                    |
|----------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------|
| Vignette (corners)   | `radial-gradient(ellipse at center, transparent 55%, rgba(0,0,0,0.35) 100%)`                       |
| Light leak (off-axis)| `radial-gradient(circle at 20% 30%, rgba(200,146,60,0.10) 0%, transparent 60%)`                    |
| Surface fade (top)   | `linear-gradient(to bottom, var(--bg-warmBlack) 0%, transparent 100%)` — used **only** for nav scrim |

### Forbidden gradient patterns
- ❌ Linear gradients across the whole viewport (decorative).
- ❌ Conic gradients.
- ❌ Multi-color gradients (sunset, instagram, bisexual lighting).
- ❌ Animated gradient hue shifts.
- ❌ Trendy "pastel mesh" gradients.
- ❌ Webkit `background-clip: text` rainbow text.

---

## 6. Chapter Palettes

Each canonical chapter type has a default palette. Chapters may override but must stay within the system's tokens.

### `hero` palette (default)
- Background: `bg.warmBlack`
- Text: `text.cream`
- Accent: `accent.parchment`
- Tint: `tint.warmFog` at 6%
- Light leak: warm, upper-left, intensity 0.06

### `editorial` palette (default)
- Background: `bg.paper`
- Text: `text.primary`
- Accent: `accent.slate`
- Tint: `tint.coolPaper` at 4%
- Light leak: none

### `case` palette (default)
- Background: `bg.warmBlack` or `bg.cream` (alternates by case)
- Text: `text.cream` / `text.primary`
- Accent: `accent.copper` (warm cases) / `accent.slate` (cool cases)
- Tint: matched
- Light leak: directional, intensity 0.04

### `human` palette (default)
- Background: `bg.cream`
- Text: `text.primary`
- Accent: `accent.moss`
- Tint: `tint.coolPaper` at 3%
- Light leak: none — pure stillness

### `cultural` palette (default)
- Background: `bg.warmBlack` or `bg.charcoal`
- Text: `text.cream`
- Accent: `accent.amber` or `accent.ember`
- Tint: `tint.amberDust` at 6%
- Light leak: warm, intensity 0.08
- WebGL palette tint: `tint.amberDust`

### `closing` palette (default)
- Background: `bg.warmBlack` (regardless of preceding chapter)
- Text: `text.cream`
- Accent: none
- Tint: `tint.warmFog` at 4%
- Light leak: faint, fading to dark

